-- Butler Upsets No. 1 Indiana 88-86 in Overtime on Barlow’s Shot
-- B y   A a r o n   K u r i l o f f
-- 2012-12-16T05:01:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-16/butler-upsets-no-1-indiana-88-86-in-overtime-on-barlow-s-shot.html
Alex Barlow hit a 6-foot shot with
two seconds remaining in overtime to help Butler University beat
college basketball’s top-ranked  Indiana  University 88-86 in
Indianapolis yesterday.  Barlow, a sophomore walk-on, finished with a career-high
six points for Butler (8-2). Rotnei Clark added 19 points and
Roosevelt Jones had 16 points, 12 rebounds and seven assists.  Cody Zeller scored 18 points for Indiana (9-1), including a
layup that tied the score with fewer than 20 seconds left in
overtime. Victor Oladipo also had 18 points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Kuriloff in  New York  at 
 akuriloff@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jim McDonald at 
